snippet.textDisplay:
At first I didn't like this music video, but actually now I am making more conneciton as we all know Shawn enjoys telling stories with imagery. So here is what I gathered; We all know the song is about Corey being abused, feeling trapped and trying to get out of the situation. (Hence the person in caccoon) So when we put this logic on Slipknot itself as whole band. Those colors that makes us go "wtf" actually representing the pop culture, luxury, fake happiness that's being pushed on our faces. Feeling trapped and they are struggling in those white box shaped rooms alone. Yet they are trying to remain alive with remaining as themselves. Slipknot is the one feeling trapped here like Corey did back in his childhood. Trying to break that caccoon surrounding them. And when we see the band in whole shot, it's the moment they see the "true" face of it. Colors are removed, band members are together. It's pure white, it's all clear now. It's broken.


That gives us all "FUCK YES" moment not only because we see the whole band together headbanging but it's also Corey found himself again to not drown in that abuse anymore. You can actually make sense of the lyrics for those both situaitons. - Most people didn't like imagery in this music video because what they see here represents what we all don't like in this world.
